Overall, I like it. But I think you've over-redacted in a couple spots. I don't think that this sentence: "The address on the letter will be altered to reflect the change in location, however no evidence of alteration is present, suggesting the use of [REDACTED]." needs anything after the last comma, for one. And I'm assuming that "Possible links to SCP-███ are currently being investigated." refers to SCP-662, and don't think it needs to be blacked out if that's the case. Also, I like the interview, but cringed at the "But had it always been there last week?" question. I can't stand behind a direct Discworld quote in a serious article.







